<subSubSection pageNumber="378" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="378">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="378">Note:</emphasis>
In the protologue, Linnaeus cited a Hermann polynomial published in a supplement by 
<bibRefCitation pageNumber="378" refId="references.r52">Burman (1737)</bibRefCitation>
. This polynomial and reference, written by Linnaeus, can be found annotating three specimens in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Hermann’s">Hermann's</normalizedToken>
herbarium (vol. 4: 16, BM). They are clearly original material for 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Linnaeus’">Linnaeus'</normalizedToken>
name and were treated as the type by Adamson.
</paragraph>
